China Police Detain Men 5 Days for Online Rumor, Xinhua Reports

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-12-12T07:05:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-12/china-police-detain-men-5-days-for-online-rumor-xinhua-reports.html
Authorities in central  China ’s  Hunan
province  will detain two men for five days for spreading a
“rumor” on the internet that 5,000 policemen and 100 police
vehicles were seen guarding a wedding convoy, the official
Xinhua News Agency reported.  The two men posted a video clip online showing crowds of
police officers and a wedding convoy on a street in Changsha,
capital of Hunan province, according to Xinhua. Police said the
officers were returning from a training session and were by
coincidence passing the wedding convoy, Xinhua reported.  The two men, both in their twenties, will be detained in
accordance with relevant laws, Xinhua reported, citing local
police officials.  To contact the reporter on this story:
